  "text": "The insensitivity to the initial beam profile makes it possible to realistically simulate the beam-shaping technique. Here, an appropriate choice for the excimer-laser beam is the GaussianSchell model (GSM), which includes both the Gaussian spatial distribution and the coherence properties of the laser beam. In GSM, the two orthogonal directions (x and y) can be handled separately, and the so-called cross spectral density function in one of the directions (here x) is given by [CITATION_1] ",
